 Syntax:  .look
          .look <room>

Results:  Given by itself gives a description of the room that you are in,
          including the people who are there, the number of messages on
          the message board, current room topic, and various other
          details. (profile) after a user's entry means they are entering
          a profile. (vote topic) after a user's entry means they are
          entering a topic to vote on. (room desc) after a user's entry
          means they are entering a room description for the current room.
          Given a <room> it does a remote look on <room>. If the room is
          secured/hidden, you must be of proper rank to view it.
